stylometry: The tradeoff/relationship between price and demand that we must consider when we are setting the price of a product or a service is that usualy on products or services that are wants and not needs as the price goes up the demand goes down and when the price goes down the demand goes up. Alot of it depends on the market and how it compares to other products being sold that are similar to yours. The management decision in this is to find the happy medium in this to still make the most profit possible while still being able to sell the product at a price that customers will still be willing to pay. A model you could use to help solve this problem would be something where you found how much it was to make the product, what your maximum spending amount was to make the products, and what the demand was, so then you could find a price that you could make a profit off of. Then take it to the market and see how it compares to other similar products.
